social_posts.post_text:
I’m still hungover from last night at Yumbo. 
I discovered the heaven known as Strong  Construction last night. Best gay cruising bar I’ve been to. I’ve never had so much fun on a night out. I don’t remember the last time I closed out a bar at 4 am. Totally worth it. Thank you boys!

I landed in Gran Canaria a little over a week ago. I was broken, damaged and full of self destroying pain. I was at my worst I had ever seen myself. My depression was at the worst It had ever been. I was going through the actions of life but I really struggled to achieve any goals or make any progress. I was barely living. I never saw joy or happiness no matter how hard I tried. I had been like this for months. I suffered in silence because I could not find the help I needed when I did open up. I had talked to several therapist and still ended each day an emotional wreck crying myself to sleep night after night. I was stuck in an endless loop with no true end in sight. I had given up ever being myself again. 

Without knowing each other for very long Dustin invited me half way around the world. Within a week this man has taught me so much about myself. He showed me how to heal and overcome my past. He has taught me so much about life. I really feel like a changed man because of him. 

I’ve healed a lot and finally I am feeling myself again. I could have never done it without the help of a friend who understands me and cared to see me get better. I’ve never known such a genuine person with a heart of gold. Thanks for all you have done Dustin.
